      "key": {
        "uuid": "92fc0499_bbdc74a9",
        "filename": "resultdb/proto/v1/recorder.proto",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 286,
      "author": {
        "id": 1147264
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-02-04T04:53:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027d not include it but did it just because https://google.aip.dev/133#request-message states \"A parent field must be included\".\n\nI\u0027m happy to remove `invocation` from `both CreateArtifactRequest` and `BatchCreateArtifactRequest`. WDYT?",
      "parentUuid": "e14203fa_cb05cbbe",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 285,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 286,
        "endChar": 29
      },
      "revId": "2a13004c5cede8545101776694311c792dbaf00e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "eceac4bc_b90f2e34",
        "filename": "resultdb/proto/v1/recorder.proto",
        "patchSetId": 7
      },
      "lineNbr": 286,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-02-04T05:16:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "ah. then we should follow those guidelines\n\n1) It should be `parent`, not invocation, because the parent could be a test result. In the latter case, it would be the test result name.\n2) There should be artifact_id field, see https://google.aip.dev/133#user-specified-ids\n3) Artifact.name must be ignored\n\nGiven that we need to be able to create artifacts in different test results (which are different parents), perhaps we should NOT have BatchCreateArtifactsRequest.parent",
      "parentUuid": "92fc0499_bbdc74a9",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 285,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 286,
        "endChar": 29
      },
      "revId": "2a13004c5cede8545101776694311c792dbaf00e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
